<div>
  <p><a href="http://www.jslint.com/">JSLint</a> plugin that allows you to run a sensible subset of jslint rules against
  your project. You can include and exclude files and specify an output file.</p>

  <p>Outputs in the <a href="http://checkstyle.sourceforge.net/">CheckStyle</a>
     format so you can integrate the JSLint results right into your build!

     You should probably use the <a href="https://wiki.jenkins-ci.org/display/JENKINS/Checkstyle+Plugin">Checkstyle plugin</a>
     to include the jslint results in your Jenkins project,</p>
     
  <p>Produced by <a href="http://www.boxuk.com">Box UK</a></p>
</div>
